HEADWORD: Bistoury
<hw>Bis"tou*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Bistouries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>bistouri</ets>.]</ety> <def>A surgical instrument consisting of a
slender knife, either straight or curved, generally used by introducing
it beneath the part to be divided, and cutting towards the
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

